<F P=100> AUSTRALASIA </F>
<F P=101> Australia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Welcomes End to U.S. Trade Embargo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0402013994 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 0100 GMT 4 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0402013994 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Australia has welcomed the U.S. decision to lift its 
embargo on Vietnam. A spokesperson for the foreign minister, 
Gareth Evans, said although the decision does not include the 
establishment of diplomatic relations, it is a positive step 
toward Vietnam's acceptance in the international community. The 
spokesperson says the increased competition which is likely to 
result between Australian and U.S. firms in Vietnam should also 
be welcomed. 

</TEXT>

