Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, February 6 (KCNA) -- Representatives of 
nine South Korean Peasants Organisations including the National 
Federation of Peasants Associations (Chonnong) jointly called a 
press conference on February 4 and opposed again the farm market 
opening, according to a radio report from Seoul. 
  They demanded that the puppet authorities leave the blanks 
of 
