<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, February 6 (KCNA) -- The foreign minister 
of the Republic of Cuba, Roberto Robaina Gonzalez, in a 
solidarity message to his Korean counterpart Kim Yong-nam, 
reaffirmed the invariable support and active solidarity of Cuba 
for the arduous struggle of the Korean people for socialist 
construction and the independent and peaceful reunification of 
the country, the supreme desire of the nation. 
  "The Cuban people will always express solidarity with the 
Korean people in their efforts to fulfil the noble tasks put 
forward by President Kim Il-song in his New Year address," 
stated the message. 

