<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Remains of 13 U.S. Servicemen Returned </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0802150894 Hanoi VNA in English 1454 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0802150894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA Feb. 8 -- The Vietnam MIA office yesterday 
handed over to the representatives of the US military Joint Task 
Force on the MIA issue 13 remains of the American servicemen and 
personal effects relating to 26 American militarymen reported 
missing in the Vietnam war. 
  It is the first handover since US President Bill Clinton's 
decision to lift the trade embargo on Vietnam last week. And 
since March 1974, Vietnam has on 46 occasions returned the 
remains of 593 American servicemen to the US side. 
  Of the 13 remains returned yesterday, six were collected by 
the Vietnam-US joint search teams during the 27th joint search 
operation for MIAs and seven handed over by the local people. 
  The US side appreciated the humanitarian policy and 
cooperation of the Vietnamese Government and people in settling 
the MIA issue. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

