<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Radio Reports Returned Remains </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0802112694 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam in English 1000 GMT 8 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0802112694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vietnam has handed over to the U.S. the remains of 
12 U.S. servicemen reported missing in the Indochina war. Head 
of the Hanoi Task Force for MIA Colonel John Cray said the 
lifting of the embargo created more favorable conditions for his 
job in Vietnam. He also believed that Vietnam would now more 
actively cooperate with the U.S. to solve the MIA issue. 

</TEXT>

