<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia Urges Action Against Border Violations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0602082094 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 5 Feb 94 
Morning Edition p 3 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0602082094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] It was learned on 4 February that Colonel General 
Andrey Nikolayev, commander of the Russian Border Security 
Force, in an unofficial visit to the Ministry of Foreign Affairs 
[MOFA], asked the Japanese Government to take appropriration 
actions against Japanese boats engaging in "illegal fishing 
operations" around the northern territorial islands. 
  According to an official concerned, Commander Nikolayev 
visited the MOFA on 3 February to meet with officials of the 
MOFA and the Maritime Safety Agency. At the meeting, he warned 
that Russia will take measures to ban Japanese boats from 
fishing in Russian waters in the future, saying: "Such acts 
cannot be tolerated because it is a violation of Russian 
borders." The MOFA insisted there was no problem because these 
northern territories are Japan's territories. But the Russian 
commander said emphatically: "No peace treaty has been concluded 
with Japan yet, and Russia's borders with Japan are existing 
facts." 

</TEXT>

