<H3> <TI>   Demands Hosokawa Approve Purchase </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0402114194 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 4 Feb 94 
Morning Edition p 7 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0402114194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In the morning of 3 February, Defense Agency [DA] 
Director General Kazuo Aichi met with Prime Minister Hosokawa at 
the prime minister's official residence. Regarding the expense 
in purchasing an airborne warning and control system (AWACS), 
which the DA is demanding to be included in a budget for fiscal 
1994, Aichi pointed out, among other things, the need to give 
consideration to Japan-U.S. relations. He demanded that the 
expenses be included in the budget, saying: "I want the 
expenses to be approved when the Finance Ministry's draft budget 
will be unofficially announced. The ministry is scheduled to do 
that on 10 February prior to your trip to the United States." 

