<H3> <TI>   NDP Not To `Cooperate' With Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0302164794 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1325 GMT 3 Feb 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0302164794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, February 3 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The main 
force of the political opposition in the country the Mongolian 
National Democratic Party [NDP] has given up its intention to 
cooperate with the government formed by the Mongolian People's 
Revolutionary Party two years ago. The leadership of the party 
announced the other day about its refusal of their suggestions 
having been submitted to the prime minister last autumn. The 
twelve points of those suggestions included some particular 
ideas designed at the way out of the crises for the national 
economy. 
  The repudition of any intentions to cooperate with the 
government the party explains by that the governmental programme 
has fully been discredited the government itself has been 
steeped in corruption and abuses of official position which 
relates to its top level most. [sentence as received] As a 
pretext for such statements served the recent statement by chief 
of the counterintelligence colonel L. Sanjaasuren. He accused 
the chairman of the parliament, his deputy and the premier of 
the government of criminal liaison with citizens of China 
working, according to the data available in this office, for the 
secret services of the southern neighbour. 

</TEXT>

