<F P=101> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials Deny Corruption Allegations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0502181194 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1456 GMT 5 Feb 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0502181194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, February 5 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- Lately 
in the mass media there is a great deal of talks about 
involvement of high officials of the Mongolian parliament and 
the government in corruption, bribery and abuse of power, 
proceeding from the statement made by the former chief of 
counterintelligence of the State Security Central Department, 
Colonel L. Sanjaasuren at the press conference organized by him. 
  Apropos of this the government press service organized today 
a press conference to give an opportunity to the officials 
involved in the case to speak on the question and to give 
corresponding explanations themselves. The chairman of the 
Supreme Court Dembereltseren, the chief of the Central Customs 
Department Seseer, the Prime Minister's Adviser Bayarbaatar, the 
Vice-President of Mongolbank Chuluunbat, the Department Chiefs 
of the Ministry of Trade and Industry Altantulga, Shashnaabazar, 
the director of the company "Mongol Mark" /"Mongolian Stamp"/ 
Radnaabazar gave explanations and answered questions of 
journalists. 
  The above mentioned persons refuted the statement of Colonel 
L. Sanjaasuren about involvement of the prime minister and the 
parliament chairman and vice-chairman and other officials in 
corruption, bribery and abuse of power. 

</TEXT>

