<F P=100> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Border Agreement Signed With Russia, China </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2701160594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1458 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2701160594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Kim Boldokhonov] </F>
  [Text] Ulaanbaatar January 27 TASS--An inter-governmental 
agreement between Mongolia, Russia and China on the 
determination of junction points of state borders of the three 
states has been signed in the capital of Mongolia today. This 
was a result of joint strenuous work of experts for a year 
because border issues demanded urgent settlement. 
  The adoption of a such a document for the first time is an 
evidence of strengthening of mutual respect, sovereignty of each 
of the member states and the development of friendly relations 
between them, as well as the positive changes in international 
relations as a whole. 
  The conclusion of this agreement means for us that Mongolia 
has reached a full agreement on state border issues and thus 
laid the foundation of its stability, Zhalbuugiin Choinkhor, 
Mongolian minister of foreign relations, told ITAR-TASS. 
  Russia and China with respect to Mongolia demonstrated 
respect for such important international principles as 
inviolability of its state borders, its independence and 
territorial integrity. The historical importance of the present 
agreement lies just in all this, the Mongolian minister of 
foreign relations stressed. 

</TEXT>

