<F P=100> AUSTRALASIA </F>
<F P=101> Papua New Guinea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rebel Attack Leaves One Dead in Bougainville </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1002063094 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 0500 GMT 
10 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1002063094 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] There have been two new clashes between Papua New 
Guinea [PNG] security forces and the Bougainville Revolutionary 
Army [BRA] in which one person was reported to have been killed 
and three wounded. PNG Radio said the first clash occurred when 
the BRA attacked the government station at Boku in Southeast 
Bougainville yesterday morning. The radio said one of the 
rebels was killed in an exchange of fire with troops guarding 
the station. In the second clash, three civilians, including a 
senior public servant, were wounded when rebels ambushed two 
government vehicles travelling from Sovele to (?Koto). One of 
the vehicles was abandoned and later set on fire by the rebels. 
PNG Radio said the clashes are part of step-up attacks by the 
BRA in government- controlled areas of Bougainville. 

</TEXT>

