<H3> <TI>   Auto Parts Official on U.S. Demand for Targets </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0902042494 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 9 Feb 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0902042494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 9 February Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] Yukio Itagaki, chairman of the Japan Auto Parts 
Manufacturers' Association (and president of Zexel Corporation), 
gave a speech at the Foreign Correspondents' Club of Japan in 
Tokyo on 8 February. Speaking about the U.S. demands at the 
Japan-U.S. Government talks on setting numerical targets with 
respect to procurement of auto parts, Itagaki noted, "business 
volume is bound to change depending on economic conditions." He 
cast doubts on the rationale for the U.S. Government's rigid 
position, saying "the government should not interfere in purely 
private business dealings." 
  He also said "not-externally-forced, voluntary cooperative 
relations should be established between Japan and the United 
States." 

</TEXT>

