<H4>   Syria's Al-Shar' Demands Action </H4>
<F P=102> JN0902173494 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1615 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0902173494 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The states of the Nonaligned Movement opened 
their consultative meeting in Jakarta this morning. Foreign 
Minister Faruq al-Shar' participated in this meeting. In his 
comments, al-Shar' called for activating the movement's stands 
and decisions in order to take part in formulating international 
resolutions and resolving regional and international problems in 
the current international situation. 
  Within this framework, the foreign minister denounced the 
barbaric massacre against Muslim Bosnians. He demanded that the 
world community not accept just an expression of regret and 
concern but take a measure to end this continued tragedy. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

